[30;1m1946 | [0m[35m      </h2>[0m
[30;1m1947 | [0m[35m<p id="section-8-1">Currently, a "VALARM" is triggered when a specific date-time value is[0m
[30;1m1948 | [0m[35m      reached. It is also desirable to be able to trigger alarms based[0m
[30;1m1949 | [0m[35m      on location, e.g., when arriving at or departing from a[0m
[30;1m1950 | [0m[35m      particular location.<a href="#section-8-1" class="pilcrow">¬∂</a></p>[0m
[30;1m1951 | [0m[35m<p id="section-8-2">This specification adds the following elements to "VALARM"[0m
[30;1m1952 | [0m[35m      components to indicate when an alarm can be triggered based on[0m

[30;1m714 | [0m[35mAll the functionality of ``recurring-ical-events`` can be extended and modified.[0m
[30;1m715 | [0m[35mTo understand where to extend, have a look at the `Architecture`_.[0m
[30;1m716 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m717 | [0m[35mThe first place for extending is the collection of components.[0m
[30;1m718 | [0m[35mComponents are collected into a ``Series``.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m636[0m[34m of [0m[33m912[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m699 | [0m[35mEach icalendar **Calendar** can contain Events, Journal entries,[0m
[30;1m700 | [0m[35mTODOs and others, called **Components**.[0m
[30;1m701 | [0m[35mThose entries are grouped by their ``UID``.[0m
[30;1m702 | [0m[35mSuch a ``UID`` defines a **Series** of **Occurrences** that take place at[0m
[30;1m703 | [0m[35ma given time.[0m
[30;1m704 | [0m[35mSince each **Component** is different, the **ComponentAdapter** offers a unified[0m
[30;1m705 | [0m[35minterface to interact with them.[0m
[30;1m706 | [0m[35mThe **Calendar** gets filtered and for each ``UID``,[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m637[0m[34m of [0m[33m912[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m

[30;1m503 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m504 | [0m[35mAll the functionality of ``recurring-ical-events`` can be extended and modified.[0m
[30;1m505 | [0m[35mTo understand where to extend, have a look at the `Architecture`_.[0m
[30;1m506 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m507 | [0m[35mThe first place for extending is the collection of components.[0m
[30;1m508 | [0m[35mComponents are collected into a ``Series``.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m702[0m[34m of [0m[33m912[0m[31m ]--[0m
